By Ugochi Ugochukwu Abuja – A 23-year-old carpenter, Abdulhadi Saleh, 0n Monday appeared  in a Zuba Upper Area Court, Abuja, for allegedly assaulting his neighbour with a shovel. Saleh, who resides at Dutse Makaranta by Obasanjo Road Abuja, is charged with defamation of character, assault and causing grievous hurt. The Prosecution Counsel, Mr Chinedu Ogada, told the court that the matter was reported on June 11, at Dutse Police Station, Abuja, by Adamu Ibrahim, Ogada alleged that at about 1 p.m., Saleh attacked the complainant during an an altercation over a missing empty bucket of paint. He alleged that the defendant, inflicted deep cuts on the complainant’s head, hand and right leg. ”The complainant is presently receiving medical treatment at the Kubwa General Hospital,” he said. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of sections 392, 265 and 247 of the Penal Code. The Judge, Alhaji Gambo Garba, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N50, 000 with one surety in like sum and adjourned the case until July 3 for hearing.